The paper deals with learning bilingual word embeddings, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning techniques for learning these embeddings, which suggests that it may fall under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of document-aligned comparable data, which is a common source of data for cross-lingual NLP tasks, suggesting that it may also fall under the categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of dense real-valued word vectors, which is a common technique in deep learning, suggesting that it may also fall under the category of cs.DL (Machine Learning).
